== Latin ==

=== Etymology ===

:Derived from [[querquetum]], "oak forest"; [[quercus]], "oak".

=== Adjective ===

'''querquetulanus''' ([[querquetulana]], [[querquetulanum]])

# [[oak]]-[[forested]]; covered by an oak [[forest]]

==== Notes ====

'''mons querquetulanus''' is an old name of the [[w:Caelian Hill|Caelian Hill]], one of the seven hills of Rome.

